2022 Gachon University BK21 Winter School
The purposes of the school
This winter school is aimed at providing early education to the incoming researchers who are going to join
the graduate studies. The lecture series provide fundamentals of some selected fields, which help the
researchers to grasp the big pictures of the fields and determine their own research topics and issues.
Time schedule and class method
The winter school will be held between end of Dec 2020 and end of Feb 2021. Majority of the classes will
be given in the afternoon or evening (local time in Korea) to accommodate difference in time zone. This
is because many incoming graduate students will be joining the class from different countries (e.g.
Pakistan). Classes will be given online in pre-recorded or live form. Pre-recorded online classes will be
delivered using YouTube, but live online classes using video conference tools such as Webex or Zoom.

Prof. Seong Oun Hwang (Gachon University, South Korea)

Hyung Jin Chang (University of Birmingham, UK)
Lecture 1. Human-Centred Visual Learning and Its Applications
Abstract: One of the ultimate goals of AI research is to make humans lives better by creating intelligent
systems that are similar to or better than people. In that sense, humans are the best teachers as well as
beneficiaries for AI development. Human-centred visual learning is an approach to develop vision-based
algorithms that aim to make systems usable and useful by focusing on humans, especially their needs and
requirements. In this talk, I will introduce my recent research on human-centred vision tasks, including
human attention mimicking visual object tracking, attention driven image cropping, real-time hand pose
& gaze tracking, and human body movement retargeting, and so forth. Also, some interesting applications
using the human-centred vision methods will be presented.
Lecture 2. Computer Vision Research Trends, Paper Writing, and Useful Tips
Abstract: Computer vision research is one of the hottest fields these days. Focusing on research keywords
that are recently presented in top-tier conferences, we will look at the current research trends, and not
only the research topics but also the trends in research methodologies. Also, I will share my know-how
how to write papers to be submitted to top-tier conferences (CVPR, ICCV, ECCV, etc.) that have been made
through my own experiences, and how reviews are conducted at the top conferences. Besides, various
tips for conducting computer vision research and creating research networks will be introduced.

Title: Applying Data Sciences for Healthcare and Reinforcement Learning
2.
Pre-requisite:
None
Textbook (if applicable):
Data Science Concepts and Techniques with Applications, by Qamar, Usman and Raza,
Muhammad Summair (https://www.springer.com/gb/book/9789811561320
3.
Mode of Delivery: Lecture and Practical Sessions
4.
Professor/Researcher: Associate Professor Dr Usman Qamar (NUST, Pakistan)
5.
Objectives of Unit:
1. Connecting machine learning, big data analytics, statistics, pattern recognition,
computer vision, and Semantic Web technologies to healthcare applications.
2. Highlight the successful application of these technologies in reinforcement learning.
3. Intended for data scientists involved in the healthcare.
6.
Synopsis of Unit:
The lecture will promote the exploitation of data science in healthcare systems. The
focus is on advancing the automated analytical methods used to extract new knowledge
from data for healthcare applications. To do so, the lecture will draws on several
interrelated disciplines, including machine learning, big data analytics, statistics, pattern
recognition, computer vision, and Semantic Web technologies, and focuses on their
direct application to healthcare and reinforcement learning.
Building on tutorials on data science in healthcare, the lecture will highlight success
stories on the application of data science in healthcare, where data science and artificial
intelligence technologies have proven to be very promising. By attending this lecture,
they will gain essential insights into the modern data science technologies needed to
advance innovation for both healthcare businesses and patients.
7.
Equipment and Software Required (if any):
a) RapidMiner (https://rapidminer.com/educational-program/)

Topic 1: Data Science in Healthcare: Benefits, Challenges
and Opportunities
Data Science has played a vital role in the healthcare to
predict the patterns that help in curing contagious, long-
lasting diseases using fewer resources. Extracting
meaningful information and pattern from the data collected
through the patients history stored in hospital, clinics, and
surgeries help the doctors to refine their decision making and
advise best medical treatment that helps the nations to live
longer than before.
3
Topic 2: Introduction to Classification Algorithms and
Their Performance Analysis Using Medical Examples
Majority of machine learning algorithms these days are
based on supervised machine learning techniques. Although,
it is a complete domain which requires separate in depth
discussion, here we will only provide a brief overview of the
topic.
3
Topic 3: The Role of Deep Learning in Improving
Healthcare
We shall focus on Deep Learning (DL), a subfield of ML that
relies on deep artificial neural networks to deliver
breakthroughs in long-standing AI problems. DL is about
working with high-dimensional data (e.g., images, speech
recording, natural language) and learning efficient
representations that allow for building successful models.
3
Topic 4: Clinical Natural Language Processing with
Deep Learning
The huge amount of data inspires research and development
focused on novel clinical natural language processing (NLP)
solutions to optimize clinical care and improve patient
outcomes. Here we will present an overview of how deep
learning techniques can be applied to solve NLP tasks in
general, followed by a literature survey of existing deep
learning algorithms applied to clinical NLP problems.
3
Topic 5: Making Effective Use of Healthcare Data Using
Data-to-Text Technology
Healthcare organizations are in a continuous effort to
improve health outcomes, reduce costs, and enhance patient
experience of care. Data is essential to measure and help
achieving these improvements in healthcare delivery.
Consequently, a data influx from various clinical, financial,
and operational sources is now overtaking healthcare
3
organizations and their patients. The effective use of this
data, however, is a major challenge. Clearly, text is an
important medium to make data accessible.
Topic 6: Data Visualization in Reinforcement Learning
Here we present direct data visualization techniques, along
with their limitations and directions for future research into
readily interpretable, unbiased data visualizations for
reinforcement learning.
3
Topic 7: Using Process Analytics to Improve
Reinforcement Learning
Process mining is a emerging research area combining data
science (machine learning, data mining, etc.) and business
process management. Its main contributions have been
techniques for process discovery (the automatic learning of
process models from event data) and conformance checking
(aligning observed and modeled behavior).
3
Topic 8: RapidMiner I
Introduction to RapidMiner and example of classification
algorithms and performance analysis using medical
examples.
3
Topic 9: RapidMiner II
Examples of clustering algorithms and performance analysis
using medical examples and data visualization.

Synopsis of Unit:
The lectures are designed to provide a deep insight of the information security
compliance evaluation and auditing process. The theme mainly emphasizes on two
main contents i.e. security compliance and Auditing. Compliance module will familiarize
students about the security risk assessment and evaluation organizations security
posture and guidance for related security controls deployment with respect to ISO
standards. Auditing contents will provide the learning process of audit services in
accordance with security audit standards that will ultimately help to assist the
organization in protecting and controlling their information systems.

Synopsis of Unit:
The class awakens the importance of basic as well advance concepts in machine
learning and deep learning from two perspectives; generative and discriminative
perspectives. Furthermore, this provides the basic concept of finding the similarities in

such as classification. This course also emphasize the importance of deep learning
approaches in comparison to classical machine learning approaches.
